WEBVTT

00:02.197 --> 00:04.398
Leonard, what time does
your mom's plane get in?

00:04.400 --> 00:05.966
I don't know--
some time tomorrow morning.

00:05.968 --> 00:07.868
Don't you want
to know for sure?

00:07.870 --> 00:10.371
No need to. As soon as she flies
into California airspace,

00:10.373 --> 00:12.439
I'll feel a disturbance
in the Force.

00:14.075 --> 00:16.110
It's so nice
both of your moms are coming in

00:16.111 --> 00:17.611
to see you guys get an award.

00:17.613 --> 00:21.015
Well, my mother's been there
for every honor I've won

00:21.017 --> 00:22.549
since I beat out my twin sister

00:22.551 --> 00:24.485
for the "did it
on the potty" trophy.

00:26.021 --> 00:27.454
How does this look?

00:27.456 --> 00:29.923
Aw, it's so nice.
She's gonna love it.

00:29.925 --> 00:31.191
Sure, his mom gets roses.

00:31.193 --> 00:32.393
When I want them,

00:32.395 --> 00:35.329
they're a "bouquet of
severed plant genitals."

00:36.364 --> 00:37.765
You act like I didn't get you

00:37.767 --> 00:40.100
that mushroom log
on Valentine's Day.

00:40.102 --> 00:41.468
He's right.

00:41.470 --> 00:45.139
Roses die, but a moist rotting
log will pump out mushrooms

00:45.141 --> 00:47.641
for two or three magical years.

00:47.643 --> 00:49.643
You know,
your mom's never been

00:49.645 --> 00:50.911
too thrilled
with our relationship.

00:50.913 --> 00:52.713
Maybe I should get her something
so she warms up to me.

00:52.715 --> 00:54.415
If you could run
out and get a PhD,

00:54.417 --> 00:56.984
that might make
her like you.

00:56.986 --> 01:00.287
Really?
It didn't work for you.

01:00.289 --> 01:01.789
Do you think
the moms will get along?

01:01.791 --> 01:03.490
Uh, I don't know.
They're pretty different.

01:03.492 --> 01:05.358
Maybe they'll be best friends.

01:05.361 --> 01:08.395
One of them is brilliant,
one is sweet and simple.

01:08.397 --> 01:11.165
Sound familiar?

01:11.167 --> 01:14.802
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:14.804 --> 01:18.138
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:18.140 --> 01:19.740
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:19.742 --> 01:22.276
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:22.278 --> 01:24.978
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:24.980 --> 01:27.581
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:27.583 --> 01:29.516
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:29.518 --> 01:30.902
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

01:30.905 --> 01:34.905
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 8x23 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Maternal Combustion</font>
